  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 21 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 6 critical, 10 high, 4 medium, 19 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI) and Rome–Fiumicino Leonardo da Vinci (FCO/LIRF); plus 13 other bases. 4 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk, low cloud base and very low visibility  — most notably around Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Modlin (WMI/EPMO) and Vilnius (VNO/EYVI). Network hotspots: Castellón-Costa Azahar (CDT/LECH), Bordeaux–Mérignac (BOD/LFBD), Al Massira (AGA/GMAD), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA) and 16 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and cold‑temperature performance penalties. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA), Dortmund (DTM/EDLW) and 9 others.",
